name: adgender
definition: A gender modality in which one is moving toward a particular gender or gender presentation.

name: na-trans
definition: The word "cisgender" was first published in the third edition of the Oxford English Dictionary (OED) in June 2015.

name: integragender
definition: A gender modality in which one has multiple genders, one of which matches their assigned gender at birth while at least one other does not, meaning that they are both cis and trans.

name: ipsogender
definition: A term used to refer to the gender modality of a cisgender intersex person.

name: transgender
definition: Transgender people have a gender identity or gender expression that differs from their assigned sex. In some select cases, transgender people are sometimes called transsexual if they desire medical assistance to transition from one sex to another. "Transgender" is also an umbrella term: in addition to including people whose gender identity is the opposite of their assigned sex (trans men and trans women), it may include people who are not exclusively masculine or feminine (people who are genderqueer or non-binary, including bigender, pangender, genderfluid, or agender). Other definitions of transgender also include people who belong to a third gender, or else conceptualize transgender people as a third gender.

name: ultergender
definition: A term used to refer to the gender modality of a transgender intersex person.
